He doesn't see it.

658
00:47:47,901 --> 00:47:50,571
Wouldn't matter if he did.

659
00:47:50,654 --> 00:47:52,149
Elvis lets me win.

660
00:47:53,366 --> 00:47:55,489
<i>Everybody lets me win.</i>

661
00:47:56,286 --> 00:47:59,240
Wait a minute. You know this game?

662
00:48:06,631 --> 00:48:08,375
THE BOSS: You got three days.

663
00:48:10,177 --> 00:48:11,969
I was thinking it would take me a week.

664
00:48:12,054 --> 00:48:14,546
Oh, you were thinking that, were you?

665
00:48:14,641 --> 00:48:18,853
With all your experience killing people?
I'll tell you what.

666
00:48:21,023 --> 00:48:23,016
You win this game, you got your week.

667
00:48:27,614 --> 00:48:28,279
Hm.

668
00:48:38,836 --> 00:48:41,754
THE BOSS: So, what's the plan with Yitzchok?

669
00:48:43,216 --> 00:48:45,008
Was gonna play it by ear.

670
00:48:45,093 --> 00:48:48,261
Well, if it's all the same,
I'd write it down. It's a tough tune.

671
00:48:49,807 --> 00:48:51,884
And, by the way, he has shadows.

672
00:48:55,731 --> 00:48:57,558
Shadows?

673
00:49:01,655 --> 00:49:03,398
Bodyguards.

674
00:49:04,157 --> 00:49:06,197
With him all the time.

675
00:49:08,079 --> 00:49:09,953
Military.

676
00:49:15,045 --> 00:49:17,085
Ex-lsraeli Mossad.

677
00:49:18,549 --> 00:49:22,595
THE BOSS: They go where he goes,
round-the-clock. Ex-lsraeli Mossad.

678
00:49:22,679 --> 00:49:24,719
Ex-lsraeli Mossad.

679
00:49:27,352 --> 00:49:28,550
That doesn't sound good.

680
00:49:29,771 --> 00:49:32,013
<i>They live in the apartment next door.</i>

681
00:49:32,941 --> 00:49:35,231
He wears a panic button on a chain
around his neck.

682
00:49:35,319 --> 00:49:37,443
<i>Looks like an ordinary Star of David.</i>

683
00:49:38,323 --> 00:49:41,692
He presses that button
and, well, we all know how that ends.

684
00:49:41,785 --> 00:49:43,196
What's this?

685
00:49:44,372 --> 00:49:45,486
Oh, God! No, you didn't?

686
00:49:48,585 --> 00:49:50,329
- Get down!
- (Silenced gunshot)

687
00:49:52,047 --> 00:49:54,337
<i>Response time's gonna be</i>
<i>three to five seconds.</i>

688
00:49:55,093 --> 00:49:57,382
He's gonna have to hit him
when he least expects it.

689
00:49:57,470 --> 00:49:59,510
Where?

690
00:49:59,598 --> 00:50:02,434
- Where?
- The apartment.

691
00:50:03,811 --> 00:50:07,560
How do I get in his apartment?
I can't just walk in the front door.

692
00:50:08,317 --> 00:50:10,689
No, I was thinking you'd use the back door.

693
00:50:18,245 --> 00:50:20,321
Then what?

694
00:50:20,414 --> 00:50:22,656
He does the kid, I do him.

695
00:50:23,585 --> 00:50:26,158
I plant my gun. Clean, no history.

696
00:50:26,254 --> 00:50:30,419
And Yitzchok - fire a round,
get some powder burns on the hands.

697
00:50:31,803 --> 00:50:35,504
Take the clothes off- make it look like a,

