01:14:31,098 --> 01:14:33,221
It wasn't supposed to look like a job.

949
01:14:35,227 --> 01:14:40,434
So you take out the Israelis,
bomb the damn building...

950
01:14:42,275 --> 01:14:45,691
and now the job
that was not supposed to look like a job's

951
01:14:45,778 --> 01:14:48,103
beginning to look very much

952
01:14:48,197 --> 01:14:50,236
like a job.

953
01:14:59,207 --> 01:15:01,246
All right. Fuck it.

954
01:15:03,878 --> 01:15:05,917
If the Rabbi wants a war...

955
01:15:06,839 --> 01:15:09,412
...I'll give him a war.

956
01:15:16,723 --> 01:15:18,550
Saul.

957
01:15:21,269 --> 01:15:23,760
- Saul.

958
01:15:24,230 --> 01:15:26,519
<i>Saul, the phone's been...</i>

959
01:15:26,607 --> 01:15:28,647
Oh.

960
01:15:28,734 --> 01:15:30,774
I thought you were Saul.

961
01:15:33,489 --> 01:15:35,814
People have been thinking I'm somebody else.

962
01:15:39,411 --> 01:15:41,948
Your predicament reminds me of a story.

963
01:15:42,038 --> 01:15:44,493
Hitchcock. North By Northwest.

964
01:15:45,374 --> 01:15:49,288
The movie where everybody thinks Cary Grant
is a man named George Kaplan,

965
01:15:49,378 --> 01:15:52,498
but the thing is there is no George Kaplan.
It's just a made-up name.

966
01:15:52,589 --> 01:15:55,045
But names, even made-up ones...

967
01:15:57,594 --> 01:15:59,919
...can bring about quite a bit of trouble.

968
01:16:01,931 --> 01:16:03,390
Now...

969
01:16:03,474 --> 01:16:05,716
the woman in the picture with Grant,

970
01:16:05,810 --> 01:16:08,265
- <i>her name was er...</i>
- Eva Marie Saint.

971
01:16:08,354 --> 01:16:11,224
- Oh... you know this movie.
- I know this movie.

972
01:16:11,315 --> 01:16:14,518
I took my father to see it in 1959.
His English wasn't very good,

973
01:16:14,610 --> 01:16:17,563
but boy, did he like Miss Saint.

974
01:16:17,654 --> 01:16:20,571
After the movie he turned to me and he said,
"She's a real Buick."

975
01:16:20,657 --> 01:16:24,191
You see, he couldn't pronounce
the word beauty, so he'd say Buick.

976
01:16:25,536 --> 01:16:29,450
- Caused quite a bit of confusion.
- Using the wrong name'll do that.

977
01:16:33,836 --> 01:16:35,745
Is that my money?

978
01:16:35,837 --> 01:16:37,248
This is everything I owe you.

979
01:17:11,912 --> 01:17:15,862
It's the Sabbath. You see,
we don't answer the phone on the Sabbath.

980
01:17:15,958 --> 01:17:17,831
I know.

981
01:17:17,918 --> 01:17:19,791
Normally Saul turns off the ringer.

982
01:17:19,878 --> 01:17:21,076
Saul!

983
01:17:21,171 --> 01:17:23,840
I tell you, you can't find good help these days.

984
01:17:27,843 --> 01:17:30,132
Saul's dead.

985
01:17:32,931 --> 01:17:34,212
<i>They're all dead.</i>

986
01:17:58,705 --> 01:18:00,745
Oh, I've been in this room before.

987
01:18:03,293 --> 01:18:05,332
Looks the same as it did 20 years ago.

988
01:18:06,629 --> 01:18:08,668
Somehow...

989
01:18:09,548 --> 01:18:10,959
Somehow it seems different.

990
01:18:11,050 --> 01:18:14,833
The way your car seems different
when someone else is driving it.

991
01:18:16,138 --> 01:18:19,304
Then again, it's been 20 years
since I've been in a car.

992
01:18:20,600 --> 01:18:23,767
Two decades spent behind three inches
of bulletproof glass

993
01:18:23,853 --> 01:18:28,645
due to a natural fear of high-powered rifles
and quiet... rooftops in New Jersey.

994
01:18:28,733 --> 01:18:30,772
20 years...

995
01:18:32,778 --> 01:18:36,194
...locked away in my own paranoia,
a prisoner in my own home.

996
01:18:38,700 --> 01:18:41,571
Only to be delivered to fate by a boy.

997
01:18:45,331 --> 01:18:49,660
<i>Well, Anthony, it looks as though you've won,</i>
<i>if such a term may be applied.</i>

998
01:18:52,087 --> 01:18:54,459
<i>If I were wearing a hat, I would take it off.</i>

999
01:18:58,552 --> 01:19:00,176
Should we get on with it, then?

1000
01:19:06,726 --> 01:19:08,765
You can keep your hat on, Schlomo.

1001
01:19:13,941 --> 01:19:17,356
Looks like we were sold a bill of goods
by the same salesman.

1002
01:19:19,946 --> 01:19:21,986
Nice speech, though.

1003
01:19:25,868 --> 01:19:28,193
I wish I was standing for it.

1004
01:19:39,256 --> 01:19:41,497
You... you brought this upon our heads.

1005
01:19:43,885 --> 01:19:48,013
- Me?
- You... you hired Goodkat to kill my son.

1006
01:19:49,974 --> 01:19:52,013
After you murdered my son?

1007
01:19:53,811 --> 01:19:56,681
- I had no hand in that.
- Oh, sure.

1008
01:19:56,772 --> 01:19:58,811
Just like in '84?

1009
01:19:59,358 --> 01:20:02,940
I suppose you had no hand in that either.
Just a finger, maybe?

1010
01:20:05,697 --> 01:20:07,736
Time's up, Rabbi.

1011
01:20:09,367 --> 01:20:12,320
Lying to a dead man's
the same as lying to yourself.

1012
01:20:16,331 --> 01:20:18,371
You were getting too big.

1013
01:20:20,252 --> 01:20:22,291
See...

1014
01:20:23,588 --> 01:20:25,711
...problem when two men are standing in a room

1015
01:20:25,798 --> 01:20:28,716
is you can only look at one of them
and they were looking at you

1016
01:20:28,801 --> 01:20:32,300
with their backs turned,
their shirt collars smiling at me.

1017
01:20:34,974 --> 01:20:36,384
Then they called you The Boss.

1018
01:20:39,478 --> 01:20:41,517
It was clear what had to be done.

1019
01:20:48,027 --> 01:20:50,862
Try and appreciate how it feels, Schlomo...

1020
01:20:53,365 --> 01:20:57,279
...to wake up in the middle of the night
with six bullets burning in your stomach.

1021
01:20:58,161 --> 01:21:00,487
Lying in a pool of your own blood and shit.

1022
01:21:04,876 --> 01:21:06,915
The dead eyes of...

1023
01:21:10,381 --> 01:21:13,002
...of your wife... staring back at you.

1024
01:21:16,804 --> 01:21:18,843
The only thing keeping you from passing out

1025
01:21:18,931 --> 01:21:22,015
is the sound of the footsteps of the man
going down the hall...

1026
01:21:23,435 --> 01:21:25,474
...looking for your son.

1027
01:21:30,691 --> 01:21:32,731
I managed to save my son, Schlomo.

1028
01:21:34,445 --> 01:21:36,484
And now...

1029
01:21:37,656 --> 01:21:39,779
...after all these years...

1030
01:21:41,701 --> 01:21:43,243
...in spite of our agreement!

1031
01:21:44,537 --> 01:21:46,162
You... you...

1032
01:21:46,247 --> 01:21:49,248
fucking backstabbing Philistine.

1033
01:21:50,168 --> 01:21:52,326
You managed to take my son away from me.

1034
01:21:53,879 --> 01:21:55,919
Well...

1035
01:21:57,174 --> 01:21:59,297
...now I've taken your son away from you.

1036
01:21:59,384 --> 01:22:02,420
I told you I had nothing to do with...

1037
01:22:11,604 --> 01:22:13,513
You haven't heard.

1038
01:22:13,606 --> 01:22:15,645
Will I?

1039
01:22:16,233 --> 01:22:19,933
Look at my face, Schlomo. Look at my smile.

1040
01:22:21,863 --> 01:22:23,571
Your son is dead.

1041
01:22:26,951 --> 01:22:29,109
Your son is dead.

1042
01:22:31,789 --> 01:22:34,410
I'm gonna kill you. Hm.

1043
01:22:36,752 --> 01:22:37,866
SLEVIN: <i>Rabbi.</i>

1044
01:22:39,171 --> 01:22:41,247
<i>Are you familiar with the Shmoo?</i>

1045
01:22:53,601 --> 01:22:55,640
Fisher.

1046
01:22:57,521 --> 01:22:59,560
Fisher, listen to me.

1047
01:23:02,400 --> 01:23:04,974
I already told you,

1048
01:23:05,070 --> 01:23:07,109
I'm not Nick Fisher.

1049
01:23:12,451 --> 01:23:14,491
Then who is Nick Fisher?

1050
01:23:21,001 --> 01:23:22,958
I think you mean, who was Nick Fisher?

1051
01:23:24,629 --> 01:23:26,503
Fisher was the answer to a question.

1052
01:23:26,589 --> 01:23:29,341
How do you get to two men
that can't be gotten to?

1053
01:23:37,307 --> 01:23:39,347
<i>You get them to come to you.</i>

1054
01:23:47,358 --> 01:23:49,896
<i>But to do that... I needed a name.</i>

1055
01:23:50,736 --> 01:23:52,895
<i>And where do you find names?</i>

1056
01:23:52,989 --> 01:23:55,064
<i>In books.</i>

1057
01:23:59,453 --> 01:24:01,030
<i>And who has books?</i>

1058
01:24:09,128 --> 01:24:11,168
<i>Well, your bookies have books.</i>

1059
01:24:13,007 --> 01:24:14,169
He's clean.

1060
01:24:14,258 --> 01:24:16,297
SLEVIN: <i>Crooked bookies...</i>

1061
01:24:17,136 --> 01:24:20,220
- <i>... who work with big-time crooks.</i>
- So... why are you here?

1062
01:24:31,899 --> 01:24:33,643
<i>I was looking for a gambler.</i>

1063
01:24:35,277 --> 01:24:37,021
O<i>ne who was in both books...</i>

1064
01:24:37,780 --> 01:24:40,152
<i>... with a lot of red in the minus column.</i>

1065
01:24:40,240 --> 01:24:41,403
Got him.

1066
01:24:41,491 --> 01:24:43,531
<i>And that's when I found Nick Fisher.</i>

1067
01:24:44,160 --> 01:24:46,283
<i>A lowlife that no-one was gonna miss.</i>

1068
01:24:47,997 --> 01:24:49,373
1729.

1069
01:24:49,457 --> 01:24:51,699
Nick Fisher.

1070
01:24:51,792 --> 01:24:53,832
OK.

1071
01:25:05,555 --> 01:25:07,594
GOODKAT: <i>There was a time.</i>

1072
01:25:24,322 --> 01:25:26,943
All that was left to do was make the phone ring.

1073
01:25:47,510 --> 01:25:51,259
<i>All I had to do was pull the trigger</i>
<i>and wait for you to call the man</i>

1074
01:25:51,347 --> 01:25:53,672
<i>who does thejobs that no-one else wants.</i>

1075
01:25:55,810 --> 01:25:57,849
THE BOSS: <i>I want an outsider brought in.</i>

1076
01:25:59,313 --> 01:26:01,519
There's a specialist.

1077
01:26:03,733 --> 01:26:05,809
Calls himself Mr Goodkat.

1078
01:26:11,866 --> 01:26:13,905
Fine.

1079
01:26:15,619 --> 01:26:17,861
Tell him he can expect me in the morning.

1080
01:26:22,542 --> 01:26:24,582
Are you ready?

1081
01:26:24,669 --> 01:26:26,709
Yeah.

1082
01:26:29,799 --> 01:26:31,838
It's just that one last thing.

1083
01:26:40,809 --> 01:26:42,220
THE BOSS: <i>Mr Goodkat.</i>

1084
01:26:43,228 --> 01:26:44,936
It's been a long time.

1085
01:26:49,275 --> 01:26:53,937
I'm sorry to have kept you waiting, Mr Goodkat.
So I'll get right down to business.

1086
01:26:55,072 --> 01:26:58,939
Slim Hopkins, the man who ran my book,
was hit yesterday.

1087
01:27:00,661 --> 01:27:02,902
And I guess you've already heard about...

1088
01:27:04,414 --> 01:27:07,035
- <i>... my son.</i>
- Yes, I heard.

1089
01:27:08,042 --> 01:27:09,869
I need you to sort it out for me.

1090
01:27:09,961 --> 01:27:11,669
Who's the mark?

1091
01:27:11,754 --> 01:27:13,332
Yitzchok.

1092
01:27:16,717 --> 01:27:18,342
Yitzchok, The Rabbi's son?

1093
01:27:18,427 --> 01:27:20,633
<i>You remember The Rabbi?</i>

1094
01:27:20,721 --> 01:27:22,547
I remember The Rabbi well.

1095
01:27:22,639 --> 01:27:24,264
<i>Thing is...</i>

1096
01:27:24,349 --> 01:27:26,887
it can't look like a job.

1097
01:27:27,811 --> 01:27:30,348
<i>If Yitzchok gets hit, The Rabbi will go to war.</i>

1098
01:27:32,940 --> 01:27:37,353
So... I need you to make it look like
it ain't what it is.

1099
01:27:38,904 --> 01:27:41,110
<i>Can that be done?</i>

1100
01:27:41,198 --> 01:27:43,190
Anything can be done.

1101
01:27:45,452 --> 01:27:47,824
Good. How?

1102
01:27:47,912 --> 01:27:50,071
Kansas City Shuffle.

1103
01:27:51,874 --> 01:27:53,831
I'm not familiar with the term.

1104
01:27:56,629 --> 01:27:58,787
I'll need to see Slim's books.

1105
01:27:58,881 --> 01:28:04,467
Slim's books were taken when he was hit,
but... I do keep copies.

1106
01:28:09,224 --> 01:28:11,430
What are you looking for?

1107
01:28:14,896 --> 01:28:17,565
This is our guy. Nick - 1729.

1108
01:28:18,232 --> 01:28:20,355
1729.

1109
01:28:20,442 --> 01:28:21,853
Nick Fisher.

1110
01:28:21,944 --> 01:28:23,058
Why him?

1111
01:28:24,196 --> 01:28:25,856
A loser.

1112
01:28:25,947 --> 01:28:28,236
Pick him up. Bring him here.

1113
01:28:36,791 --> 01:28:39,163
GOODKAT: <i>Still not talking to each other, huh?</i>

1114
01:28:39,251 --> 01:28:41,291
<i>Can't say that I blame you.</i>

1115
01:28:41,378 --> 01:28:43,536
- Why are you here?
- Big job.

1116
01:28:43,630 --> 01:28:46,714
I was under the impression
you no longer worked New York.

1117
01:28:46,800 --> 01:28:49,966
Like I said... very big job.

1118
01:28:50,053 --> 01:28:54,264
And you thought, as long as you're in town,
you'd drop by and see your old pal Schlomo,

1119
01:28:54,348 --> 01:28:57,135
and say, "Hello. How about them Yanks?"

1120
01:28:59,520 --> 01:29:01,559
No. But something like that.

1121
01:29:05,734 --> 01:29:08,688
Only problem is you and I aren't old friends.

1122
01:29:08,778 --> 01:29:10,272
And I hate baseball.

1123
01:29:10,363 --> 01:29:13,648
And since we're not friends and
you hate baseball, why the fuck are you here?

1124
01:29:13,741 --> 01:29:16,612
It's because we're not friends that I'm here.

1125
01:29:17,536 --> 01:29:21,285
Because if we had been friends,
I wouldn't have been hired to kill your son.

1126
01:29:21,373 --> 01:29:26,118
Because that is right at the top of my list
of things that friends do not do to their friends.

1127
01:29:26,211 --> 01:29:29,461
The good news for you is,
my friendship is for sale.

1128
01:29:30,256 --> 01:29:33,625
You see, it seems to me
that your son means more to you alive

1129
01:29:33,718 --> 01:29:35,710
than he does to The Boss dead.

1130
01:29:35,803 --> 01:29:38,045
And more money means more to me
than less money.

1131
01:29:38,139 --> 01:29:42,266
And you are the guy that sleeps with
all that green under your mattress.

1132
01:29:43,101 --> 01:29:44,679
I'm listening.

1133
01:29:44,770 --> 01:29:48,849
You will pay me double to kill The Boss
what The Boss was paying me to kill Yitzchok.

1134
01:29:48,940 --> 01:29:52,143
- Ohh.
- And that...

1135
01:29:53,945 --> 01:29:55,984
And that will make us friends.

1136
01:29:56,781 --> 01:29:58,820
Right, Rabbi?

1137
01:29:59,909 --> 01:30:01,284
Hm?

1138
01:30:05,414 --> 01:30:10,159
And... since friends do favours for their friends,
you will do a favour for me.

1139
01:30:10,251 --> 01:30:13,169
Pray tell? What is this favour?

1140
01:30:13,254 --> 01:30:16,789
Concerns a matter of debt collection.
One debt in particular.

1141
01:30:16,882 --> 01:30:18,045
Whose?

1142
01:30:18,134 --> 01:30:21,253
A flop. From Benny's book.
Goes by the name of Nick Fisher.

1143
01:30:21,345 --> 01:30:23,503
Who is he?

1144
01:30:23,597 --> 01:30:25,636
Just a loser.

1145
01:30:25,724 --> 01:30:27,763
You just made a lot of money.

1146
01:30:31,229 --> 01:30:34,432
SLEVIN: <i>And then I was free</i>
<i>to come and go as I pleased.</i>

1147
01:30:48,370 --> 01:30:49,200
Hm?

1148
01:30:49,287 --> 01:30:52,371
Whatever they're paying you...

1149
01:30:59,213 --> 01:31:00,624
Oh.

1150
01:31:01,548 --> 01:31:02,793
There is nobody.

1151
01:31:05,135 --> 01:31:07,174
I did this to you.

1152
01:31:10,181 --> 01:31:11,379
- Me.
- You.

1153
01:31:12,141 --> 01:31:13,933
Me.

1154
01:31:20,065 --> 01:31:22,105
Who are you?

1155
01:31:24,778 --> 01:31:26,771
BRIKOWSKl: <i>Who is he?</i>

1156
01:31:26,863 --> 01:31:31,192
Considering he no longer has fingerprints,
I'd say it's unlikely we'll ever know.

1157
01:31:31,284 --> 01:31:33,111
What about dental records?

1158
01:31:33,202 --> 01:31:38,789
Sure, find the bottom half of the jaw, then all
we need to do is find out who the dentist was.

1159
01:31:39,625 --> 01:31:41,664
What a fucking mess.

1160
01:31:43,045 --> 01:31:45,417
<i>Hey, Brikowski, it's Marty, you there?</i>

1161
01:31:45,505 --> 01:31:49,585
<i>We found two more bodies</i>
<i>to go along with the two you've already got.</i>

1162
01:31:49,676 --> 01:31:51,715
All right, I'll be right over.

1163
01:31:51,803 --> 01:31:56,132
Did you ever get a hold of The Rabbi so he can
get down here and identify what's left of his kid?

1164
01:31:56,224 --> 01:31:59,592
<i>Negative.</i>
<i>We've been calling for the last hour, no answer.</i>

1165
01:31:59,685 --> 01:32:01,179
Send somebody over.

1166
01:32:01,270 --> 01:32:02,468
<i>Copy.</i>

1167
01:32:04,481 --> 01:32:07,316
You all right? You look a little shook-up.

1168
01:32:07,400 --> 01:32:09,274
No, I'm fine.

1169
01:32:09,361 --> 01:32:11,400
All right.

1170
01:32:34,842 --> 01:32:38,045
- Yeah.
- <i>Hey, Brikowski, it's Murphy.</i>

1171
01:32:38,137 --> 01:32:39,715
Hey, Murph, what's up?

1172
01:32:39,805 --> 01:32:42,925
<i>Harry Kello came by today.</i>
<i>You remember Harry?</i>

1173
01:32:43,017 --> 01:32:46,884
He retired a few years ago. His wife just died,
so he comes in a couple of times a week,

1174
01:32:46,978 --> 01:32:49,018
talks shop, tells stories to the rooks.

1175
01:32:49,105 --> 01:32:52,806
Starts every sentence with, "The way
things used to be". Guy living in the past.

1176
01:32:52,901 --> 01:32:55,474
- Yeah. Yeah, what about him?
- <i>We're making small talk.</i>

1177
01:32:55,570 --> 01:32:59,188
Guy says he can't complain,
then all he does is fuckin' complain.

1178
01:32:59,281 --> 01:33:02,697
His dead wife, the leg he got shot in,
his crappy pension,

1179
01:33:02,785 --> 01:33:06,485
but then he stops when he sees the picture
Marty snapped of your kid.

1180
01:33:06,580 --> 01:33:10,411
Just stares at it.
I say, "What is it? You know the kid?"

1181
01:33:10,500 --> 01:33:13,252
Thing is, he ain't looking at the picture,
but at the name.

1182
01:33:13,336 --> 01:33:16,752
I've got it written at the bottom.
He knows that name: Slevin.

1183
01:33:36,816 --> 01:33:38,855
I have that same phone.

1184
01:33:51,329 --> 01:33:55,706
<i>About an hour later the phone rings, it's Harry,</i>
<i>talking like a goddamned machine gun,</i>

